'''Botshabelo''', meaning "a place of refuge", is a large black settlement set up by the then [[apartheid]] government 45&nbsp;km east of [[Bloemfontein]], [[Free State]] province, [[South Africa]]. Population is mainly composed of people speaking [[Sotho language|Southern Sotho]] and [[Xhosa language|Xhosa]].
